3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with knowledge amalgamation and expertise mastery, which are related to AI. 
4. cs.RO (Robotics) is a less likely category, but still possible as scene parsing and depth estimation are important tasks in robotics. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a less likely category, but possible as the paper deals with training a deep-model using a novel strategy.
